    "SUMMARY OFJTHE WEEK Conarresslonal In the Senate on the 21st a petition was presented and referred from members of the Georgia Constitutional Convention asking Con trress to establish provisional governments for the South A series of resolutions were offered and laid on the table that the Presilent be directed to cause an investigation into the arrest of American citizens by the British Government and that if done without cause to demand their immediate release and if necessary to call out the land and naval forces to enforce the demand A bill was introduced and referred to fund the public debt and amend the banking laws of the United States A resolution was adopted re questing the President to inform the Senate whether James A Seddon was Secretary of the Confederacy any portion of the time when Henry Wirz was keeper of Andersonviile prisonlbe resolution for the admission of Philip Francis Thomas Senator elect from Maryland was lain over until the 23d The Supplementary Recon struction bill came from the Bouse and was re ferred Adjourned In the House on the 21st a majority report from the Committee on Elections was made against the admission to seats of either John Young"
